al anthem.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is known for his love of performing his own high-octane stunts, from jumping out of planes to climing to the top of the Burj Khalifa, and it seems Paris was no exception in the exhilarating display.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 897, \"end\": 902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999693046, \"rank\": 3.062567497249203e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an extra clip, Tom then flew to Los Angeles before skydiving to the ground and heading straight to the Hollywood sign, which featured Olympic rings, before he jumped down it.\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 987, \"end\": 998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999868080068, \"rank\": 1.3157595032241447e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1058, \"end\": 1072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He encountered US cyclist Kate Courtney, who took the flag from him before passing onto Olympic champion Michael Johnson and then skateboarding Jagger Eaton.\", \"from\